# TypeScript Standards

See [docs/CODING_STANDARDS.md](../../docs/CODING_STANDARDS.md) for full detail.

- Use strict mode; avoid `any`; prefer `unknown` when type is unknown.
- **Naming**: camelCase for vars/functions, PascalCase for types/classes.
- **Errors**: Use typed error classes with inheritance; include context (cause, code).

```typescript
// Good
class NotFoundError extends AppError {
  constructor(resource: string, id: string) {
    super(`Resource not found: ${resource} (${id})`, { code: 'NOT_FOUND' });
  }
}
```

- Add TSDoc for all public (exported) APIs.
